---
description: Apply when writing or refactoring logic in src/
globs: src/**/*.py
---
# Security Standards
- NEVER use `assert` for production logic; use `if not condition: raise ValueError()`.
- All functions must have Type Hints (Python 3.12+ syntax).
- Check for hardcoded secrets (Gitleaks compliance).
- When adding libraries, run `pip-audit` to verify the supply chain.
- If a security vulnerability is found, STOP and report it.
